==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Magneto-electrical
<hw>Mag`net*o-e*lec"tric*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or characterized by,
electricity by the action of magnets; <as>as, <ex>magneto-electric</ex>
induction</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Magneto-electric machine</b></col>, <cd>a form of
dynamo-electric machine in which the field is maintained by permanent
steel magnets instead of electro-magnets.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magneto-electricity</ent>⟦br⟧
